# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ASST — root environment template
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in what
# you actually need. Every var is optional; the only hard rule
# is that the provider matching your orchestrator model must
# have its key set (Ollama / local: do not need a key).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Orchestrator model (optional) ────────────────────────────
# Format: <provider>:<model>[@<baseUrl>]
# Examples:
#   google:gemini-2.5-flash            (default)
#   openrouter:nvidia/nemotron-nano-9b-v2:free
#   openai:gpt-4o-mini
#   ollama:llama3.1                    (no key needed)
#   local:mistral-7b@http://localhost:1234/v1
#
# ASST_ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL=google:gemini-2.5-flash

# ── LLM provider keys (set only what you use) ────────────────
GOOGLE_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Base URLs for OpenAI-compatible / local-model providers
# (leave unset if you're using the providers' defaults)
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# ASST_LOCAL_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1
# ASST_LOCAL_API_KEY=

# ── Solana on-chain data ─────────────────────────────────────
# Used by assurance-tools/solana-rpc-read and related tools.
# SOLANA_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com
# SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet

# Helius (apps/chain-intake, optional Enhanced APIs)
# HELIUS_API_KEY=
# WATCH_ADDRESS=
# WEBHOOK_SHARED_SECRET=

# Postgres (apps/chain-intake)
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@localhost:5432/asst

# ── Skill retrieval (optional) ───────────────────────────────
# Each sub-agent already bakes 2–3 pinned skills into its system
# prompt. Setting this to N > 0 tells the engine to additionally
# TF-IDF-rank the rest of .agents/skills/ for each invoke() and
# splice the top N matches into the user message. Default: 0 (off).
# Sub-agents can override this per-agent via SubAgentConfig.retrievalTopK.
# ASST_SKILL_RETRIEVAL_TOPK=2

# ── Security / HITL knobs ────────────────────────────────────
# Set ASST_ALLOW_WRITE=0 to force-deny mutating tools everywhere.
# Set ASST_WEB_ALLOW_WRITE=1 on the web server ONLY for trusted
# private deployments (default: disabled).
# ASST_ALLOW_WRITE=1
# ASST_WEB_ALLOW_WRITE=0

# ── Sandbox backend (mutating tools only) ────────────────────
# Every side-effecting tool runs through a SandboxBackend. `host`
# is the default (execa on the operator's machine) and matches
# the legacy behavior. `docker` spins up a throwaway container
# per command with a bind mount; requires Docker Desktop / docker
# on PATH. See packages/engine/src/sandbox/README.md for the
# full backend catalog (incl. deepagents Daytona/Modal adapters).
# ASST_SANDBOX_BACKEND=host                   # host | docker
# ASST_CMD_TIMEOUT=60000                      # ms — per-command
# ASST_CMD_MAX_BYTES=10485760                 # bytes — stdout+stderr cap
# ASST_SANDBOX_DOCKER_IMAGE=alpine:3.20
# ASST_SANDBOX_DOCKER_NETWORK=none            # none | bridge | host
# ASST_SANDBOX_DOCKER_MEMORY=512m
# ASST_SANDBOX_DOCKER_CPUS=1.0

# ── MCP / Cursor integration ─────────────────────────────────
# (No extra env required; @asst/mcp-server reads the same keys
#  above. Point Cursor at apps/mcp-server/dist/server.js.)

# ── CI / Colosseum Copilot scan (optional) ───────────────────
# COLOSSEUM_COPILOT_PAT=
